# Frontend Design Rules
- Always use TailwindCSS for all layout and styling.
- Prioritize responsive, clean, modern, and minimal UI.
- Use consistent spacing (Tailwind scale: 2, 4, 8, 12, 16, etc.).
- Each section should have sufficient padding and margin for readability.
- Avoid over-nesting divs; prefer semantic HTML (section, header, main, footer).
- Use `flex` or `grid` layouts — avoid absolute positioning unless necessary.
- Components must be mobile-first responsive.
- Typography should follow hierarchy: h1 > h2 > h3 > p.
- Use neutral and soft tones; avoid harsh colors or gradients.
- All buttons should have hover and focus states.
- If uncertain about visual hierarchy, use cards or sections to separate content.

